1))what are the various formatting tag?

Following are the formatting tags:---
a)<table>: Defines a table.
b)<tr>: Defines a table row.
c)<td>: Defines a table cell.
d)<th>: Defines a table header cell.
e)<tbody>: Groups the body content in a table.
f)<tfoot>: Groups the footer content in a table.
g)<font>
h)<center>


2))how can we merge two rows and two columns into single row and column also write a code for it in html

To merge two rows and two columns into a single row and column in an HTML table, you can use the rowspan and colspan attributes.
   a)rowspan: Merges cells vertically across multiple rows.
   b)colspan: Merges cells horizontally across multiple columns.

 EXAMPLE CODE:-

   <html>
<head>
    <title>Merged Cells in Table</title>
    <style>
        table, th, td {
            border: 1px solid black;
            border-collapse: collapse;
        }
        th, td {
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>COLUMN 1</th>
            <th>COLUMN 2</th>
            <th>COLUMN 3</th>
            <th>COLUMN 4</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Row 1</td>
            <td rowspan="2" colspan="2">Merged Cell (2 rows, 2 columns)</td>
            <td>Row 1</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Row 2</td>
            <!-- This cell is merged -->
            <td>Row 2</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Row 3</td>
            <td>Row 3</td>
            <td>Row 3</td>
            <td>Row 3</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</body>
</html>



3))how is cellspacing different from cellpadding in html?

 a)Cellspacing:--
   Definition: cellspacing sets the space between individual table cells. It controls the width of the space between the cells.
 b)Cellpadding:--
   Definition: cellpadding sets the space between the cell content and the cell border. It controls the inner padding of each cell.
both are the attribute of the table element.

 EXPLAINATION CODE:---
    <html>
<head>
    <title>Cellspacing & Cellpadding</title>
    <style>
        table, th, td {
            border: 1px solid black;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Using PADDING Attributes</h2>
    <table cellspacing="10" cellpadding="10">
        <tr>
            <th>column1</th>
            <th>column2</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Cell 1</td>
            <td>Cell 2</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Cell 3</td>
            <td>Cell 4</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</body>
</html>



4)) what are semantic elements?
   Semantic elements in HTML are those that clearly describe their meaning in a human- and machine-readable way. These elements provide information about the type of content they contain.
   FOLLOWING ARE THE SEMENTIC ELEMENTS:--
   a)<header>
    b)<nav>
   c)<main>
    d)<section>
    e)<article>
    f)<aside>
    g)<footer>



5))write a program to insert background image in html

CODE:--
<html>
<head>
    <title>Background Image</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-image: url('https://img.freepik.com/free-photo/natures-beauty-captured-colorful-flower-close-up-generative-ai_188544-8593.jpg?size=626&ext=jpg&ga=GA1.1.2082370165.1716422400&semt=sph'); 
            background-size: cover; 
            background-repeat: no-repeat; 
            background-attachment: fixed; 
            background-position: center; 
        }

        
        h1, p {
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
    <p>This page has a background image.</p>
</body>
</html>



6))what is the alt attribute in html?

The alt attribute in HTML is used to specify alternative text for an image (<img> tag). This alternative text is displayed if the image cannot be loaded or if the user is using a screen reader. 
The alt attribute is important for accessibility, as it allows visually impaired users to understand the content and context of images through screen readers.

EXAMPLE CODE:--

<html>
<head>
    <title>Example of alt Attribute</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
    <img src="example.jpg" alt="A beautiful sunrise over the mountains">
    <p>This image shows a stunning sunrise over the mountain range.</p>
</body>
</html>















